# Task: lay

Make the robot lay down flat on the ground from its standing position. A quadruped lay is characterized by:
- All four legs tuck under the body so the torso rests on the ground.
- The body should be flat — minimal roll and pitch.
- Base height is as low as possible, close to the ground.

